On Mac OS X system-wide JAR files, such as those for Xalan, go in
/Library/Java/Extensions

The build script moves the update.jar file to ~/Library/Java/Extensions
and copies the application properties file, update.prop, to ~/.java

To run the javadoc tool and document all methods and variables (including
private) use something like the following:

$ javadoc -d doc -private *.java

